
[1]cruelly

   CRUELLY, adv.

   1. In a cruel manner; with cruelty; inhumanly; barbarously.

   Because he cruelly oppressed, he shall die in his iniquity. Ezekiel 18.

   2. Painfully; with severe pain, or torture; as, an instrument may cut
   the flesh most cruelly.
